{
  "topicId": "m4-t2",
  "title": "At the Supermarket",
  "dialect": "fusha",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Supermarket and Shopping"
        },
        "text": "When you go to buy groceries, you typically visit a 'supermarket'. Learning these basic words will help you begin your shopping trip.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "سوبر ماركت",
            "english": "supermarket",
            "transliteration": "sūbar mārcat"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "تسوق",
            "english": "shopping (noun/gerund)",
            "transliteration": "tasawwuq"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أتسوق",
            "english": "I am shopping",
            "transliteration": "anā atasawwaq"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Basic Groceries: Bread, Milk, Eggs"
        },
        "text": "Let's learn some of the most common items you might buy at a supermarket: bread, milk, and eggs.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "خبز",
            "english": "bread",
            "transliteration": "khubz"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "حليب",
            "english": "milk",
            "transliteration": "ḥalīb"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بيض",
            "english": "eggs",
            "transliteration": "bayḍ"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What do you want?'"
        },
        "text": "When a shop assistant asks you what you want, they will use one of these phrases, depending on your gender. Notice the subtle difference in the ending vowel.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ماذا تريد؟",
            "english": "What do you want? (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "mādhā turīd?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'd' in 'تريد' has a sukoon. The ending is silent for a male."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "ماذا تُريدين؟",
            "english": "What do you want? (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "mādhā turīdīn?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'd' in 'تُريدين' has a kasra, followed by 'ya' and 'noon' with a fatḥa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أنا ذاهب إلى السوبر ماركت لأتسوق.",
        "english": "I am going to the supermarket to shop.",
        "transliteration": "anā dhāhib ilā as-sūbar mārcat li-atasawwaq."
      },
      "context": "Using 'supermarket' and 'to shop'."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أريد خبزاً وحليباً وبيضا.",
        "english": "I want bread, milk, and eggs.",
        "transliteration": "urīd khubzan wa ḥalīban wa bayḍan."
      },
      "context": "Listing common grocery items after 'I want'."
    },
    {
